Leli bandla, eliseCape Town, lisolwa ababhekene nokuvikela amalungelo ezingane. Basola umfundisi Lavender Hill ngokuba yingxenye yohambo lwentsha yaleli lokuya eBotswana. Leli bandla selivikele umfundisi walo ngokuthi lithi ngeke limmise engakatholwa  enecala. UNksz Lucinda Evans, ongusihlalo weCommunity Policing Forum (CPF)  olwela amalungelo abesifazane nezingane eMitchells Plain, uthe isenzo sebandla sisho ukuthi ohlukunyeziwe aqhubeke nokuzithola esenkingeni. Okhulumela amaphoyisa u-André Traut ukuqinisekisile ukuthi kunecala elivulwe esiteshini samaphoyisa iSteenberg, nokuthi selivele lisenkantolo. Umfundisi usolwa ngokudlwengula umfundi kaGrade 12 waseSeawinds. Ngokuka Nksz Evans, iyamcasula indaba yokungahlonishwa kokuphepha kwezingane. “Sibe nombhikisho, senzela ukuthi angabi yingxenye yentsha ethatha lolu hambo. Sizwe kamuva ibhasi isihambile ukuthi uthathwe ndawana thile uma usanda kuphuma eCape Town,” kusho yena. UNobhala we-OAC esifundeni esikule ndawo uMnuz Edrick Ipland, uthe udaba useludlulisele kumphathi omkhulu ebandleni. Uthe sebenolwazi ngaleli cala. Ukuvumile ukuthi umfundisi ube yingxenye yabathabathe uhambo oluya eBotswana. “Emuva kokuthi sithole lo mbiko, ubengakatholakali enecala. Siyayihlonipha imithetho yezwe,” kuchaza u-Ipland. Khonamanjalo umfundisi waseGeorge kule ndawo, u-Areal Haarder owayengumholi we7th Day Adventist Church ePacaltsdorp, unikezwe isigwebo seminyaka emibili evalelwe ekhaya, wagwetshwa ukusebenzela umphakathi  yiThembalethu Regional Court ngokuhlukumeza ngokocansi intombazane eneminyaka engu-10. Lokhu kuqinisekiswe okhulumela iNational Prosecuting Authority ezweni uMnuz Eric Ntabazalila.  